Package: pointapply
Type: Package
Title: Package to apply point functionality to real and synthetic data
Year: 2021
Version: 0.1.0.9001
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Martin", 
           family = "Schobben", 
           email = "schobbenmartin@gmail.com",
           role = "cre", 
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-8560-0037"))
Maintainer: Martin Schobben <schobbenmartin@gmail.com>
Description: This package accompanies the paper: New methods to detect isotopic heterogeneity with Secondary Ion Mass Spectrometry, by Martin Schobben, Michiel Kienhuis, and Lubos Polerecky. This paper revolves around the point function diag_R() which allows an assessment of isotopic heterogeneity in SIMS analyses. The package ensures the complete reproduction of this work.
